HEADWORD: Halogen
<hw>Hal"o*gen</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*j⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"a`ls</grk>, <grk>"alo`s</grk>, salt + <ets>-gen</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>halog⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
electro-negative element or radical, which, by combination with a metal,
forms a haloid salt; especially, chlorine, fluorine, bromine, and
iodine; sometimes, also cyanogen. See <cref>Chlorine family</cref>,
under <er>Chlorine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halogenous</ent>⟦br⟧
